configset GLOBAL request_answer = [value]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
GLOBAL means you are setting site parameters, not just one list
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

(extracted on 7 Mar 1999 from configshow-comments, default value is below)

# request_answer       /majordomo,owner,response/
# (majordomo)          [enum] <general>
# This variable controls what happens to messages sent to the
# 'listname-request' address.  The possible valies, and their effects:
#
# majordomo - the message will be processed for commands
# owner     - the message will be sent to the list owner
# response  - the contents of the file 'request_reply' will be returned
#             to the sender of the message.
configset GLOBAL request_answer = owner

==> see also: configset     (for an overview and list of all variables)
==> see also: configedit    (to set the variable to a non-default value)
==> see also: configshow    (to display the variable's current value)
==> see also: configdefault (to have the variable track the default value)

